Receives an email address, name and password and, if don't exist an user with this email, creates a new customer. Else, returns a response with status 409.


```response:201
{
	"detail": "User created with success"
}
```

```response:409
{
	"detail": "User already exists"
}
```

Returns the logged-in customer information based on the access token in request header. 
If the token is invalid returns a response with status 401.

```response:200
{
	"customer": {
		"email": "customer0@gmail.com",
		"name": "customer0",
		"address": {
			"id": 1,
			"street_name": "street_name",
			"house_number": 89,
			"city": "city",
			"state": "AC"
		}
	}
}
```

```response:401
{
	"detail": "Given token not valid for any token type",
	"code": "token_not_valid",
	"messages": [
		{
			"token_class": "AccessToken",
			"token_type": "access",
			"message": "Token is invalid or expired"
		}
	]
}
```

```response:401
{ 
	"detail": "Unauthorized access" 
}
```

